cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.IT, cs.CC

This paper deals with rough set theory, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of measures and axioms, which are common in the fields of data mining (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC) as it deals with the efficiency of rough set approximations.
